WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:18.101 --> 00:00:20.520
{\an8}All right. everybody. settle down!

3
00:00:22.105 --> 00:00:23.063
{\an8}Good.

4
00:00:23.064 --> 00:00:25.190
{\an8}Now. Robby has something
important to say.

5
00:00:25.191 --> 00:00:26.650
I know that this isn't easy.

6
00:00:26.651 --> 00:00:28.736
We're going to help you
address any challenges

7
00:00:28.737 --> 00:00:30.237
that you might be having.

8
00:00:30.238 --> 00:00:32.114
If you have any concerns.
just raise your hand.

9
00:00:32.115 --> 00:00:34.867
- Emma. write all this down.
- Dr. Mohan.

10
00:00:34.868 --> 00:00:37.119
Medication orders aren't coming up
from the pharmacy.

11
00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:40.456
Check with the clinical pharmacist
to see if it's in the PDS.

12
00:00:40.457 --> 00:00:44.168
If it's not. then give the third copy
of the order sheet to Dr. Nordt.

13
00:00:44.169 --> 00:00:45.919
We're gonna need more people
to run it down.

14
00:00:45.920 --> 00:00:48.631
- We'll work on it. Langdon.
- I can't find the patient clipboards.

15
00:00:48.632 --> 00:00:51.050
Clipboards need to stay here
for orders and labs.

16
00:00:51.051 --> 00:00:52.468
Wait. so how do we write our notes?

17
00:00:52.469 --> 00:00:55.471
Take the T sheet to the bedside.
not the whole chart.

18
00:00:55.472 --> 00:00:57.306
Same goes for nursing notes.

19
00:00:57.307 --> 00:00:59.099
- Princess.
- Fax machine is down.

20
00:00:59.100 --> 00:01:01.477
- Error message E6.
- What the hell does that mean?

21
00:01:01.478 --> 00:01:03.729
- You can check the manual.
- There isn't one.

22
00:01:03.730 --> 00:01:05.689
Okay. Perlah. why don't you take
your phone out to the base?

23
00:01:05.690 --> 00:01:07.692
See if you can get service.
find a manual online.

24
00:01:12.155 --> 00:01:13.697
What else? Ogilvie. put your hand down.

25
00:01:13.698 --> 00:01:16.033
- Santos.
- We've gotten a few CT results back

26
00:01:16.034 --> 00:01:17.451
but nothing on plain films.

27
00:01:17.452 --> 00:01:19.119
That's probably
because they're all sitting

28
00:01:19.120 --> 00:01:21.288
on the portable machine
not getting to radiology.

29
00:01:21.289 --> 00:01:22.998
- I'll take care of this.
- You be patient.

30
00:01:22.999 --> 00:01:25.001
Help each other. Thank you.

31
00:01:26.002 --> 00:01:27.586
We need to call in extra help.

32
00:01:27.587 --> 00:01:30.422
At 3:00 p.m. on a holiday?
I know people. buddy.

33
00:01:30.423 --> 00:01:33.425
I have a 32-year-old woman
with severe abdominal pain.

34
00:01:33.426 --> 00:01:35.135
- Do we have a bed?
- Not at the moment.

35
00:01:35.136 --> 00:01:36.303
- I'll take her.
- Incoming.

36
00:01:36.304 --> 00:01:37.471
Thank you.

37
00:01:37.472 --> 00:01:39.181
Santos. Javadi. you're up.

38
00:01:39.182 --> 00:01:40.725
Trauma one's open.

39
00:01:41.851 --> 00:01:43.268
12-year-old Jude Augustin...

40
00:01:43.269 --> 00:01:45.938
firecracker exploded.
nondominant left hand.

41
00:01:45.939 --> 00:01:47.898
Good vitals. 25 of fent so far.

42
00:01:47.899 --> 00:01:48.816
Any other injuries?

43
00:01:48.817 --> 00:01:50.651
No. but seems to have
lost two of his fingers.

44
00:01:50.652 --> 00:01:52.194
- Did you bring 'em?
- Blown to bits.

45
00:01:52.195 --> 00:01:54.029
- It really hurts.
- I'm sure it does.

46
00:01:54.030 --> 00:01:55.864
We'll do something for that.

47
00:01:55.865 --> 00:01:57.659
- Parents?
- Not on scene.

48
00:02:00.161 --> 00:02:01.078
Ready?

49
00:02:01.079 --> 00:02:03.038
One. two. three.

50
00:02:03.039 --> 00:02:06.667
Hey. Jude. do you know your mom
or your dad's telephone number?

51
00:02:06.668 --> 00:02:09.086
No. But I know my sister's.

52
00:02:09.087 --> 00:02:10.171
Okay.

53
00:02:10.880 --> 00:02:13.257
- Good breath sounds.
- Abdomen nontender.

54
00:02:13.258 --> 00:02:14.633
Heart rate 112.

55
00:02:14.634 --> 00:02:16.009
Put this around his left forearm.

56
00:02:16.010 --> 00:02:17.344
- Is that good?
- That is very good.

57
00:02:17.345 --> 00:02:20.681
I want to do another 25 of fent
before we open this bandage.

58
00:02:20.682 --> 00:02:22.433
Can you tell us what happened?

59
00:02:22.434 --> 00:02:25.310
- My friends had firecrackers.
- 25 fent on board.

60
00:02:25.311 --> 00:02:28.021
I lit one. and it went off fast.

61
00:02:28.022 --> 00:02:30.107
I-I dropped it. but...

62
00:02:30.108 --> 00:02:31.942
We're gonna take
your bandage off now. okay?

63
00:02:31.943 --> 00:02:33.819
- I don't want to see.
- You don't have to.

64
00:02:33.820 --> 00:02:35.612
Just look at me.

65
00:02:35.613 --> 00:02:36.989
Okay.

66
00:02:36.990 --> 00:02:38.074
Cutting.

67
00:02:40.869 --> 00:02:42.161
Sorry.

68
00:02:42.162 --> 00:02:43.663
You're doing great.

69
00:02:46.499 --> 00:02:49.126
That looks like a lot more
than a firecracker.

70
00:02:49.127 --> 00:02:52.880
- More like an M-80 or a cherry bomb.
- It's really good that you dropped it.

71
00:02:52.881 --> 00:02:54.465
You saved the rest of your hand.

72
00:02:54.466 --> 00:02:56.175
Digits 4 and 5 avulsed.

73
00:02:56.176 --> 00:02:59.470
Distal metacarpals 4 and 5
also gone with exposed bone.

74
00:02:59.471 --> 00:03:02.181
Soft-tissue damage on the palmar aspect.
less so on dorsal...

75
00:03:02.182 --> 00:03:03.682
some burns on wound edges.

76
00:03:03.683 --> 00:03:06.227
Jude. can you bend your fingers
for me up and down?

77
00:03:08.021 --> 00:03:09.855
Really good job. Really good job.

78
00:03:09.856 --> 00:03:12.608
- How bad is it?
- You lost two fingers.

79
00:03:12.609 --> 00:03:14.902
But it seems like the rest
are gonna be okay.

80
00:03:14.903 --> 00:03:17.322
Oh. no. I fucked up!

81
00:03:18.114 --> 00:03:19.865
All right. can we do
a wrist block for the pain?

82
00:03:19.866 --> 00:03:22.659
I want to do a very detailed
motor and sensory exam first.

83
00:03:22.660 --> 00:03:25.288
We're gonna continue
our exam now. okay. Jude?

84
00:03:28.541 --> 00:03:29.917
Okay. thanks.

85
00:03:29.918 --> 00:03:32.252
ICU can take her
after the next neuro exam.

86
00:03:32.253 --> 00:03:33.670
The ICU?

87
00:03:33.671 --> 00:03:36.299
It's just so she can be monitored
for the rest of the day.

88
00:03:37.884 --> 00:03:39.260
4 millimeters and reactive.

89
00:03:40.929 --> 00:03:42.095
Mel.

90
00:03:42.096 --> 00:03:44.765
- 4 millimeters and reactive.
- Yep. got it.

91
00:03:44.766 --> 00:03:46.643
I could sort of make out your hand.

92
00:03:50.772 --> 00:03:52.773
Can you cover your good eye?

93
00:03:52.774 --> 00:03:54.943
How many fingers am I holding up?

94
00:03:56.236 --> 00:03:57.195
Three.

95
00:03:59.322 --> 00:04:00.697
That's good news.

96
00:04:00.698 --> 00:04:03.951
So the medicine worked?
She's out of the woods?

97
00:04:03.952 --> 00:04:05.244
Possibly.

98
00:04:05.245 --> 00:04:06.370
It's...

99
00:04:06.371 --> 00:04:08.331
Okay. cover your eye again.

100
00:04:09.624 --> 00:04:11.543
{\an8}All right. what do you see?

101
00:04:12.544 --> 00:04:16.172
{\an8}- Top line is E.
- All right. and the next one?

102
00:04:18.716 --> 00:04:19.843
{\an8}Nothing.

103
00:04:20.718 --> 00:04:22.470
Okay. well. that's 20/200.

104
00:04:23.972 --> 00:04:25.472
Meaning?

105
00:04:25.473 --> 00:04:28.642
What a healthy eye can see at 200 feet.
she can see at 20 feet.

106
00:04:28.643 --> 00:04:31.603
- Is that good?
- Yeah. It's much better.

107
00:04:31.604 --> 00:04:34.357
And it can continue to improve over time.

108
00:04:35.567 --> 00:04:36.776
Thank you. Dr. King.

109
00:04:38.778 --> 00:04:41.488
I'm gonna take a quick break
before my deposition.

110
00:04:41.489 --> 00:04:44.908
So I'll let Robby know
that I'm off the clock for the time being.

111
00:04:44.909 --> 00:04:46.786
- Good luck.
- Thanks.

112
00:04:49.998 --> 00:04:51.498
- Mel.
- Hey.

113
00:04:51.499 --> 00:04:52.875
You have a visitor in chairs.

114
00:04:52.876 --> 00:04:56.044
- What? Who?
- Said she's your sister.

115
00:04:56.045 --> 00:04:57.213
Becca?

116
00:05:01.509 --> 00:05:03.302
Yep. You have heat exhaustion.

117
00:05:03.303 --> 00:05:07.139
It usually gets better with Aleve.
but today was really bad.

118
00:05:07.140 --> 00:05:08.516
Same pain you had before?

119
00:05:09.475 --> 00:05:11.727
- From a cyst?
- I think so.

120
00:05:11.728 --> 00:05:13.770
I have PCOS.

121
00:05:13.771 --> 00:05:16.440
Is the pain always on your left?

122
00:05:16.441 --> 00:05:17.816
Today it is.

123
00:05:17.817 --> 00:05:20.736
We will check a UA
and urine pregnancy test.

124
00:05:20.737 --> 00:05:22.321
and I'll give you a shot of Toradol.

125
00:05:22.322 --> 00:05:24.865
It's something a little stronger
for the pain.

126
00:05:24.866 --> 00:05:26.658
I'm not pregnant. I promise.

127
00:05:26.659 --> 00:05:29.953
No. we have to. It's hospital policy.

128
00:05:29.954 --> 00:05:32.540
You guys still write stuff down on paper?

129
00:05:33.541 --> 00:05:35.627
Today we do. yeah.

130
00:05:43.134 --> 00:05:46.345
Are you a doctor?
I've been waiting hours to be seen.

131
00:05:46.346 --> 00:05:47.554
Quick question...

132
00:05:47.555 --> 00:05:50.433
- Hey. watch the walker.
- This thing is useless.

133
00:05:51.267 --> 00:05:52.976
Sorry. I just...

134
00:05:52.977 --> 00:05:55.855
We're really busy.
and someone will see you in a second.

135
00:05:58.191 --> 00:06:00.276
- Becca.
- Mel. hi.

136
00:06:01.277 --> 00:06:04.029
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah. I have a stomachache.

137
00:06:04.030 --> 00:06:05.906
Did you see the residential-care nurse?

138
00:06:05.907 --> 00:06:08.450
She was out for the Fourth.
but I talked to her on the phone.

139
00:06:08.451 --> 00:06:10.869
She told me to come here.
and Geri brought me.

140
00:06:10.870 --> 00:06:12.287
- Thank you.
- No problem.

141
00:06:12.288 --> 00:06:14.456
- I'll wait for you.
- Okay.

142
00:06:14.457 --> 00:06:15.875
Okay. Come on. this way.

143
00:06:16.876 --> 00:06:18.126
Just through here.

144
00:06:18.127 --> 00:06:22.005
- Is it always like this?
- Yeah. pretty much.

145
00:06:22.006 --> 00:06:25.258
Wow. There are a lot of smelly people.

146
00:06:25.259 --> 00:06:26.635
Yeah.

147
00:06:26.636 --> 00:06:28.011
Are you going to help them all?

148
00:06:28.012 --> 00:06:30.222
Yeah. but let's start with you first.

149
00:06:30.223 --> 00:06:31.307
Okay.

150
00:06:32.183 --> 00:06:35.811
- How's the pain?
- I can't feel my hand anymore.

151
00:06:35.812 --> 00:06:37.020
Ancef's on board.

152
00:06:37.021 --> 00:06:40.232
Okay. we're going to clean
out your hand with saline... salt water.

153
00:06:40.233 --> 00:06:41.693
Okay.

154
00:06:45.488 --> 00:06:46.406
What's up?

155
00:06:47.115 --> 00:06:50.742
- Hand versus M-80.
- Surprised we've only seen one of these.

156
00:06:50.743 --> 00:06:52.202
The day's still young yet.

157
00:06:52.203 --> 00:06:54.413
Lost fourth metacarpal.
mid-shaft on the fifth.

158
00:06:54.414 --> 00:06:55.498
Bummer.

159
00:06:56.874 --> 00:06:59.084
Hello. I'm Dr. Garcia from surgery.

160
00:06:59.085 --> 00:07:00.752
- I'm gonna have surgery?
- Yes.

161
00:07:00.753 --> 00:07:03.422
The first operation is to clean
everything up

162
00:07:03.423 --> 00:07:05.258
and cover where the skin is missing.

163
00:07:06.009 --> 00:07:08.928
But you still have your thumb
and your most important fingers.

164
00:07:13.266 --> 00:07:15.934
- What'd you give him for pain?
- We did regional blocks.

165
00:07:15.935 --> 00:07:18.687
Hand surgery always wants to document
their own neuro exam.

166
00:07:18.688 --> 00:07:20.981
Sensation is intact
to light touch and pinprick

167
00:07:20.982 --> 00:07:23.151
throughout the digits
in the remaining hand.

168
00:07:25.528 --> 00:07:29.698
Yeah. FDS and FTPs and extensor function
was all intact.

169
00:07:29.699 --> 00:07:32.409
- Need parental consent for surgery.
- Yeah. we're working on that.

170
00:07:32.410 --> 00:07:33.536
Dr. Robby?

171
00:07:37.874 --> 00:07:39.751
I smell alcohol on his breath.

172
00:07:41.210 --> 00:07:43.795
He's in line for the OR.
Might be a little bit of a wait.

173
00:07:43.796 --> 00:07:45.088
Ortho's still in with Allen Billings...

174
00:07:45.089 --> 00:07:47.049
that open shoulder dislocation
that came back from Westbridge.

175
00:07:47.050 --> 00:07:48.300
He's still in surgery?

176
00:07:48.301 --> 00:07:50.302
He waited an hour
to be cleared by anesthesia.

177
00:07:50.303 --> 00:07:52.387
Is the insurance company
gonna cover the cost of the surgery?

178
00:07:52.388 --> 00:07:53.889
Yeah. since Westbridge is still down.

179
00:07:53.890 --> 00:07:55.223
Well. good. because the delay in care

180
00:07:55.224 --> 00:07:57.392
definitely increased the chance
of a post-op infection.

181
00:07:57.393 --> 00:08:00.396
You got to love it when insurance
companies make medical decisions.

182
00:08:01.981 --> 00:08:03.523
- Hey.
- What's up?

183
00:08:03.524 --> 00:08:06.610
Do you still need a rain check
for watching fireworks tonight?

184
00:08:06.611 --> 00:08:08.195
I thought you were coming over.

185
00:08:08.196 --> 00:08:09.572
I made other plans.

186
00:08:10.990 --> 00:08:12.407
Okay. cool.

187
00:08:12.408 --> 00:08:14.493
I'll try hitting you up tomorrow.

188
00:08:14.494 --> 00:08:16.578
We're just keeping it casual. right?

189
00:08:16.579 --> 00:08:17.789
For sure.

190
00:08:22.001 --> 00:08:24.795
Yeah. Thank you.
Yeah. bye.

191
00:08:24.796 --> 00:08:25.921
Oh. hey.

192
00:08:25.922 --> 00:08:27.714
I just got a hold of the sister
of the heavy patient

193
00:08:27.715 --> 00:08:29.341
Abbot's taking to Presby.

194
00:08:29.342 --> 00:08:30.801
She still lives in Arizona.

195
00:08:30.802 --> 00:08:33.720
but she is willing to talk
to him when he's back.

196
00:08:33.721 --> 00:08:34.805
That's good news.

197
00:08:34.806 --> 00:08:36.723
When do you think that might be?

198
00:08:36.724 --> 00:08:39.017
Depends on how crazy it is over at Presby.

199
00:08:39.018 --> 00:08:40.852
If it's anything like here. who knows?

200
00:08:40.853 --> 00:08:41.938
Yeah.

201
00:08:42.814 --> 00:08:45.232
- Is help on the way?
- Ah. ye of little faith.

202
00:08:45.233 --> 00:08:46.818
You got a gumband?

203
00:08:48.027 --> 00:08:50.238
Thanks. Keep losing these.

204
00:08:51.197 --> 00:08:52.948
Oh. this fucking day.

205
00:08:52.949 --> 00:08:55.450
Thought I was gonna get
a clean getaway for my trip.

206
00:08:55.451 --> 00:08:58.745
God gives His toughest battles
to His strongest soldiers.

207
00:08:58.746 --> 00:09:00.997
Dana. is there a room open?
This is my sister.

208
00:09:00.998 --> 00:09:03.208
She's in a lot of pain.
and we need a bed ASAP.

209
00:09:03.209 --> 00:09:04.960
My name is Becca. not "my sister."

210
00:09:04.961 --> 00:09:06.169
Sorry. right.

211
00:09:06.170 --> 00:09:09.714
Dana. Dr. Robby. this is my... Becca.

212
00:09:09.715 --> 00:09:11.007
Nice to meet you.

213
00:09:11.008 --> 00:09:14.052
You're Dr. Robby? Cool.

214
00:09:14.053 --> 00:09:16.596
Central 7 was just cleaned.
Anything I can get you. hon?

215
00:09:16.597 --> 00:09:18.057
No. thank you.

216
00:09:21.269 --> 00:09:22.854
Oh. wait. Becca. Come here.

217
00:09:23.855 --> 00:09:26.858
Come this way.
We're going right in here.

218
00:09:28.067 --> 00:09:31.027
All right. so you're gonna
need to get undressed

219
00:09:31.028 --> 00:09:33.655
and get into the gown.
which should be on the bed.

220
00:09:33.656 --> 00:09:36.366
Then we're gonna do an evaluation
and take a history.

221
00:09:36.367 --> 00:09:37.868
That's a lot of questions.

222
00:09:37.869 --> 00:09:39.911
like. like. a lot. a lot of questions.
which we'll do.

223
00:09:39.912 --> 00:09:41.663
And then a physical exam. of course.

224
00:09:41.664 --> 00:09:44.000
Mel. I've been to the doctor's before.

225
00:09:45.293 --> 00:09:46.585
Right. Sorry.

226
00:09:46.586 --> 00:09:49.672
I just... I really want this
to be done the right way.

227
00:09:53.718 --> 00:09:55.468
Do you need to take that call?

228
00:09:55.469 --> 00:09:57.846
No. it's a reminder alarm

229
00:09:57.847 --> 00:10:00.807
for this important meeting
I have in 15 minutes.

230
00:10:00.808 --> 00:10:01.976
Do you have to go?

231
00:10:03.102 --> 00:10:05.020
Let's just get you
taken care of first. all right?

232
00:10:05.021 --> 00:10:07.522
So just change into the gown.
I'll be behind the curtain.

233
00:10:07.523 --> 00:10:08.608
Okay.

234
00:10:10.151 --> 00:10:11.152
Okay.

235
00:10:21.704 --> 00:10:23.956
Your grand prize.

236
00:10:24.916 --> 00:10:27.919
All I see is green. baby.

237
00:10:36.928 --> 00:10:38.637
{\an8}What's up with her?

238
00:10:38.638 --> 00:10:40.765
{\an8}Fax machine has paper jam. so annoying.

239
00:10:49.440 --> 00:10:51.650
- You want me to try?
- No.

240
00:10:51.651 --> 00:10:54.070
- Oh. huzzah.
- I got it.

241
00:10:58.407 --> 00:10:59.908
- What's it say?
- "Replace toner."

242
00:10:59.909 --> 00:11:01.076
We live in hell.

243
00:11:01.077 --> 00:11:03.119
- Oh. where can we get that?
- 1988.

244
00:11:03.120 --> 00:11:05.664
- You ever seen one of these?
- Honestly. no.

245
00:11:05.665 --> 00:11:07.666
How are we gonna get labs
and X-rays to the wards?

246
00:11:07.667 --> 00:11:09.668
The old-fashioned way. runners.

247
00:11:09.669 --> 00:11:12.588
I'll check if they can spare
a couple clerks from upstairs.

248
00:11:17.260 --> 00:11:20.095
When were you first diagnosed
with polycystic ovarian syndrome?

249
00:11:20.096 --> 00:11:21.304
Last summer.

250
00:11:21.305 --> 00:11:23.098
That's when the symptoms started?

251
00:11:23.099 --> 00:11:26.059
No. I've had years of pain.
hormonal changes.

252
00:11:26.060 --> 00:11:27.519
and an abnormal period.

253
00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:31.648
I was finally diagnosed after switching
to a gyno who actually listened to me.

254
00:11:31.649 --> 00:11:34.026
Yeah. it can take time
to make the diagnosis.

255
00:11:35.152 --> 00:11:37.697
That sounds like an excuse
for lazy doctoring.

256
00:11:38.614 --> 00:11:41.283
And it doesn't help that some
of you don't listen to women.

257
00:11:41.284 --> 00:11:43.118
let alone brown ones.

258
00:11:43.119 --> 00:11:44.661
It hasn't been easy.

259
00:11:44.662 --> 00:11:46.830
- How's your pain now?
- Better.

260
00:11:46.831 --> 00:11:49.207
- What was she given?
- IM Toradol.

261
00:11:49.208 --> 00:11:52.377
Have you had
a transvaginal ultrasound before?

262
00:11:52.378 --> 00:11:54.212
I've lost count
of how many times.

263
00:11:54.213 --> 00:11:56.548
Okay. if you want
to scoot your bottom down.

264
00:11:56.549 --> 00:11:59.551
I'll help you put your feet
in the leg rests here.

265
00:11:59.552 --> 00:12:01.804
Yep. you got it.

266
00:12:10.313 --> 00:12:12.230
Okay. ready to go here?

267
00:12:12.231 --> 00:12:15.026
Cold gel and some pressure.

268
00:12:17.987 --> 00:12:18.988
Okay.

269
00:12:20.364 --> 00:12:25.243
Okay. ectopic is unlikely
since the urine pregnancy was negative.

270
00:12:25.244 --> 00:12:26.953
I'm hoping it'll be positive one day.

271
00:12:26.954 --> 00:12:29.497
- Oh. are you trying?
- Not at the moment.

272
00:12:29.498 --> 00:12:31.666
I'm getting married in September.

273
00:12:31.667 --> 00:12:33.669
- Oh. congratulations.
- Okay.

274
00:12:35.004 --> 00:12:38.048
A bunch of small cysts... to be expected.

275
00:12:38.049 --> 00:12:41.384
But then there's one big one.
about 5 centimeters.

276
00:12:41.385 --> 00:12:43.846
My gyno's been monitoring her.

277
00:12:45.014 --> 00:12:46.389
With a little bit of free fluid.

278
00:12:46.390 --> 00:12:49.017
Checking blood flow to the ovary.

279
00:12:49.018 --> 00:12:51.353
Red is for artery. Blue is for vein.

280
00:12:51.354 --> 00:12:53.188
Okay. looks good.

281
00:12:53.189 --> 00:12:54.690
Coming out now.

282
00:12:56.067 --> 00:12:57.068
- Sorry.
- Okay.

283
00:12:59.070 --> 00:13:02.490
We will be back when we get
your blood-test results.

284
00:13:05.242 --> 00:13:06.534
All right. what do you think?

285
00:13:06.535 --> 00:13:09.621
She probably had a small fluid leak
from the cyst that caused the pain

286
00:13:09.622 --> 00:13:12.248
that improved with a nonsteroidal.

287
00:13:12.249 --> 00:13:15.502
- And what's your plan?
- Discharge with naproxen?

288
00:13:15.503 --> 00:13:19.631
Do you think that just might be
what her doctors in the past have done?

289
00:13:19.632 --> 00:13:22.634
Well. she said she's feeling better.
We can free up a bed.

290
00:13:22.635 --> 00:13:24.010
She didn't look good in triage.

291
00:13:24.011 --> 00:13:26.846
and her pain was way more severe
than previous episodes.

292
00:13:26.847 --> 00:13:28.848
I think we observe her for a bit.

293
00:13:28.849 --> 00:13:30.433
Okay.

294
00:13:30.434 --> 00:13:33.521
Mr. Green. this is Dr. Mohan
and student doctor Ogilvie.

295
00:13:34.730 --> 00:13:36.439
What can you tell me
about your flank pain?

296
00:13:36.440 --> 00:13:39.651
- Feels like another kidney stone.
- You've had them before?

297
00:13:39.652 --> 00:13:41.820
I said "another." which means
an additional thing

298
00:13:41.821 --> 00:13:43.239
of the same type.

299
00:13:44.532 --> 00:13:46.283
I teach English at Point Park.

300
00:13:46.909 --> 00:13:48.118
Triggering.

301
00:13:48.119 --> 00:13:49.829
My dad's a high-school English teacher.

302
00:13:51.747 --> 00:13:54.375
Well. you went into medicine.
He must be really proud.

303
00:13:55.543 --> 00:13:57.210
You'd have to ask him.

304
00:13:57.211 --> 00:13:58.878
Getting back to your pain.

305
00:13:58.879 --> 00:14:01.256
it feels like something
you've experienced before?

306
00:14:01.257 --> 00:14:03.258
Same as always. left kidney.

307
00:14:03.259 --> 00:14:05.301
Started about 10:00 p.m. last night.

308
00:14:05.302 --> 00:14:06.886
Any fever. blood in the urine?

309
00:14:06.887 --> 00:14:08.763
No.
No fever.

310
00:14:08.764 --> 00:14:10.849
Urine's a bit darker than normal.

311
00:14:10.850 --> 00:14:12.809
Dehydration can lead to stone formation.

312
00:14:12.810 --> 00:14:14.394
Lean forward a bit. please.

313
00:14:14.395 --> 00:14:16.479
- Check for CVA tenderness.
- Yeah.

314
00:14:16.480 --> 00:14:17.565
All right.

315
00:14:18.941 --> 00:14:21.152
Let me know if there's any discomfort.

316
00:14:24.113 --> 00:14:25.280
- Sorry.
- Yeah.

317
00:14:25.281 --> 00:14:27.575
- We'll order medication and a few tests.
- Okay.

318
00:14:32.371 --> 00:14:35.290
Dip urine. Chem Seven.
bedside ultrasound to check for hydro.

319
00:14:35.291 --> 00:14:36.708
and ketorolac for pain.

320
00:14:36.709 --> 00:14:38.377
- Sounds good.
- Okay.

321
00:14:43.966 --> 00:14:45.425
Really putting me to work.

322
00:14:45.426 --> 00:14:47.302
It's been a very busy day. Dr. Barker.

323
00:14:47.303 --> 00:14:48.387
Call me Nick.

324
00:14:50.973 --> 00:14:53.600
- What's all this?
- I brought radiology to us.

325
00:14:53.601 --> 00:14:56.227
Dr. Barker. Nick. will have
wet-read results for us

326
00:14:56.228 --> 00:14:57.604
- in no time.
- Good idea.

327
00:14:57.605 --> 00:14:59.898
- Thank you.
- "Wet read"?

328
00:14:59.899 --> 00:15:02.984
- You ever take a photography class?
- Yeah. in. like. middle school.

329
00:15:02.985 --> 00:15:05.320
So. before digital technology. X-ray films

330
00:15:05.321 --> 00:15:08.740
were physically developed
in a darkroom. in baths. thus wet read.

331
00:15:08.741 --> 00:15:10.492
Oh. cool.

332
00:15:10.493 --> 00:15:12.411
He's taking up a lot of space.

333
00:15:13.370 --> 00:15:15.747
Got an update from Dylan
on our abandoned baby.

334
00:15:15.748 --> 00:15:18.666
CYF has requested an emergency
custody authorization.

335
00:15:18.667 --> 00:15:21.377
Once we get a court order.
we can place her in foster care.

336
00:15:21.378 --> 00:15:23.214
I love photography.

337
00:15:23.923 --> 00:15:25.048
- Jesus Christ.
- Dr. Robby?

338
00:15:25.049 --> 00:15:26.549
Dr. Robby. can I borrow you for a second?

339
00:15:26.550 --> 00:15:27.759
Sure. What can I do for you?

340
00:15:27.760 --> 00:15:29.135
Well. she said she has a stomachache.

341
00:15:29.136 --> 00:15:30.762
but belly pain can mean a lot
of different things...

342
00:15:30.763 --> 00:15:34.474
- Okay. okay. okay. breathe.
- I'm looking for Dr. Mel King.

343
00:15:34.475 --> 00:15:35.476
Yes?

344
00:15:36.560 --> 00:15:38.937
I'm Morgan Stiles.
one of the hospital's attorneys.

345
00:15:38.938 --> 00:15:41.564
I'm here to escort you upstairs
for your deposition.

346
00:15:41.565 --> 00:15:43.191
Right now?

347
00:15:43.192 --> 00:15:46.861
Morgan. can I borrow Dr. King
for just a moment?

348
00:15:46.862 --> 00:15:48.239
Sure.

349
00:15:50.032 --> 00:15:51.324
It's gonna be fine.

350
00:15:51.325 --> 00:15:53.409
I can't go up now because of Becca.

351
00:15:53.410 --> 00:15:55.578
You probably shouldn't be caring
for Becca.

352
00:15:55.579 --> 00:15:57.455
It's not a good idea
to care for family members.

353
00:15:57.456 --> 00:15:58.873
It's hard to stay objective.

354
00:15:58.874 --> 00:16:00.375
Let's see who's available.

355
00:16:00.376 --> 00:16:01.709
Hey. are you free?

356
00:16:01.710 --> 00:16:03.504
Is anybody really free?

357
00:16:04.505 --> 00:16:05.589
Not an R2.

358
00:16:06.966 --> 00:16:08.466
Just the guy we were looking for.

359
00:16:08.467 --> 00:16:10.052
- Need something?
- Yes.

360
00:16:11.053 --> 00:16:11.970
Sure.

361
00:16:11.971 --> 00:16:15.056
Dr. King's sister has a bellyache.
The case is now yours.

362
00:16:15.057 --> 00:16:16.057
Sure.

363
00:16:16.058 --> 00:16:18.393
You can pick up the rest of her patients
while she's doing her deposition.

364
00:16:18.394 --> 00:16:20.395
How am I supposed to catch up
on my outstanding charts

365
00:16:20.396 --> 00:16:22.397
with extra patients
and the computer system down?

366
00:16:22.398 --> 00:16:23.982
The same way that the rest of us do.

367
00:16:23.983 --> 00:16:26.734
You can finish your charting
when you finish your shift.

368
00:16:26.735 --> 00:16:28.654
Fucking fantastic.

369
00:16:33.284 --> 00:16:35.201
- Hi. Becca.
- Hi.

370
00:16:35.202 --> 00:16:37.620
This is Dr. Langdon.
He'll be taking care of you.

371
00:16:37.621 --> 00:16:41.624
You have really nice hair. Dr. Langdon.

372
00:16:41.625 --> 00:16:43.209
Thank you.

373
00:16:43.210 --> 00:16:46.588
Mel. would you mind turning off
the lights on your way out?

374
00:16:46.589 --> 00:16:47.673
Of course.

375
00:16:48.507 --> 00:16:50.967
And I'll be back as soon as I'm done.

376
00:16:50.968 --> 00:16:53.052
And feel free to call me
if anything comes up.

377
00:16:53.053 --> 00:16:54.846
- because I can come right...
- Don't worry.

378
00:16:54.847 --> 00:16:57.308
- Becca's in good hands.
- I know.

379
00:16:58.309 --> 00:16:59.435
Okay.

380
00:17:07.109 --> 00:17:10.112
Mel says lots of nice things about you.

381
00:17:12.239 --> 00:17:13.240
Okay.

382
00:17:15.200 --> 00:17:17.368
Tell me the reason you're here today.

383
00:17:17.369 --> 00:17:18.786
I have a stomachache.

384
00:17:18.787 --> 00:17:20.663
Your belly hurts? Where about?

385
00:17:20.664 --> 00:17:23.750
- Right down here.
- Okay.

386
00:17:23.751 --> 00:17:27.587
Are you experiencing anything else.
or is it just the stomachache?

387
00:17:27.588 --> 00:17:29.631
It stings when I pee.

388
00:17:29.632 --> 00:17:31.674
Sometimes when that happens.

389
00:17:31.675 --> 00:17:34.385
women feel like they need
to urinate all the time.

390
00:17:34.386 --> 00:17:36.179
- Do you feel that way?
- Yes.

391
00:17:36.180 --> 00:17:37.972
And what happens when you go?

392
00:17:37.973 --> 00:17:40.100
Hardly anything comes out.

393
00:17:40.768 --> 00:17:42.185
That's what I thought.

394
00:17:42.186 --> 00:17:44.729
Really? How do you know?

395
00:17:44.730 --> 00:17:47.690
Well. I've seen a lot of patients
with the same symptoms.

396
00:17:47.691 --> 00:17:50.443
- So this is normal?
- Yes. it's totally normal.

397
00:17:50.444 --> 00:17:52.820
But we still need to fix it.

398
00:17:52.821 --> 00:17:53.989
Okay.

399
00:18:00.162 --> 00:18:01.287
Hey.

400
00:18:01.288 --> 00:18:02.998
How's it going. Roxy?

401
00:18:03.624 --> 00:18:05.792
- A little better.
- Yeah?

402
00:18:05.793 --> 00:18:07.628
You need more morphine?

403
00:18:13.592 --> 00:18:16.428
I've been in pain all this time. my love.

404
00:18:17.137 --> 00:18:19.014
Why didn't you tell me?

405
00:18:20.182 --> 00:18:22.184
I didn't want you guys to worry.

406
00:18:24.144 --> 00:18:25.938
I can't pretend anymore.

407
00:18:27.606 --> 00:18:30.859
Mom. it's so hot outside.
the ice cream's melting.

408
00:18:33.821 --> 00:18:36.031
We thought we'd indulge a bit.

409
00:18:36.990 --> 00:18:38.409
Oh. yeah.

410
00:18:39.410 --> 00:18:40.284
Looks amazing.

411
00:18:40.285 --> 00:18:42.829
So which flavor should we start with?

412
00:18:42.830 --> 00:18:45.040
Salty caramel. Mom's favorite.

413
00:18:46.041 --> 00:18:48.210
You'll need lots more napkins.

414
00:19:03.976 --> 00:19:04.893
Rude.

415
00:19:07.521 --> 00:19:10.773
- How's it going in there?
- All good. Langdon's great with her.

416
00:19:10.774 --> 00:19:12.567
I got seven more films ordered.
waiting to be shot.

417
00:19:12.568 --> 00:19:14.570
but Dr. Nick here's tying up the machine.

418
00:19:15.863 --> 00:19:18.197
Isn't there a USB port
on the front of that portable?

419
00:19:18.198 --> 00:19:20.950
And can't we just download
the films to a workstation

420
00:19:20.951 --> 00:19:22.660
and watch them without the Internet?

421
00:19:22.661 --> 00:19:24.996
- Yes.
- Oh. right. Forgot about that.

422
00:19:24.997 --> 00:19:27.373
Is he actually helping.
or is he just distracting?

423
00:19:27.374 --> 00:19:29.375
Let's download these
and start moving on to folks

424
00:19:29.376 --> 00:19:31.377
- waiting for X-rays.
- Great. I'm caught up anyway.

425
00:19:31.378 --> 00:19:33.004
I'll be back when the next batch is ready.

426
00:19:33.005 --> 00:19:35.214
Dr. Robby. the guardian
of your missing-fingers kid

427
00:19:35.215 --> 00:19:37.383
- in Central 12 has arrived.
- Thank you. Olive.

428
00:19:37.384 --> 00:19:39.343
Will you ask Dr. Santos
to come and meet me. too?

429
00:19:39.344 --> 00:19:41.012
- On it.
- Who's in South 22?

430
00:19:41.013 --> 00:19:44.390
- Nobody. Headache was discharged.
- Tell that to the lady on the bed.

431
00:19:44.391 --> 00:19:45.475
What lady?

432
00:19:45.476 --> 00:19:47.810
I just tried to put
a hematuria patient in there.

433
00:19:47.811 --> 00:19:49.187
but it's occupied.

434
00:19:49.188 --> 00:19:50.730
- South 22? You sure?
- I'm positive.

435
00:19:50.731 --> 00:19:51.898
That's my patient.

436
00:19:51.899 --> 00:19:54.109
Then why isn't she on the board?

437
00:19:54.902 --> 00:19:57.278
She should be.
Olive was bringing her back from triage.

438
00:19:57.279 --> 00:19:59.614
I picked her right up.
I just assumed she made it to the board.

439
00:19:59.615 --> 00:20:01.407
You should've checked.
You should've made sure.

440
00:20:01.408 --> 00:20:02.617
I haven't put anybody on the board.

441
00:20:02.618 --> 00:20:05.203
- I thought the nurses did that.
- We all need to pitch in.

442
00:20:05.204 --> 00:20:07.622
There's no rooms at the moment.
Put hematuria on the wall.

443
00:20:07.623 --> 00:20:10.249
- Who's your patient?
- Mrs. Burns. with nausea.

444
00:20:10.250 --> 00:20:12.084
- I've ordered labs and X-rays.
- Who are you seeing her with?

445
00:20:12.085 --> 00:20:14.045
- I still need to present the case.
- Get busy.

446
00:20:14.046 --> 00:20:16.507
Find somebody with MD after their name.

447
00:20:18.509 --> 00:20:20.302
Oh. God. kids.

448
00:20:22.304 --> 00:20:25.556
Hello. I'm Dr. Robby.
This is Dr. Santos.

449
00:20:25.557 --> 00:20:27.016
- Chantal.
- How do you do?

450
00:20:27.017 --> 00:20:29.936
- We've been caring for your brother.
- Are you Jude's legal guardian?

451
00:20:29.937 --> 00:20:31.062
Yeah.

452
00:20:31.063 --> 00:20:32.856
Our parents aren't around.

453
00:20:33.857 --> 00:20:36.234
- Is he going to be okay?
- He got very lucky.

454
00:20:36.235 --> 00:20:39.487
He lost the fourth and fifth fingers
on his nondominant hand.

455
00:20:39.488 --> 00:20:42.281
But if he hadn't dropped the firecracker.
it would have been a lot worse.

456
00:20:42.282 --> 00:20:44.951
He lost fingers from a firecracker?

457
00:20:44.952 --> 00:20:47.119
Will he be able to use his hand?

458
00:20:47.120 --> 00:20:49.622
Yes. he still has
his three most important fingers.

459
00:20:49.623 --> 00:20:51.207
and they are fully functional.

460
00:20:51.208 --> 00:20:54.127
He'll need surgery to clean everything up.
but it should heal well.

461
00:20:54.878 --> 00:20:57.880
- What the fuck were you thinking?
- I'm sorry.

462
00:20:57.881 --> 00:21:00.884
Alex asked me to come over.
His brother had a stack of fire...

463
00:21:05.347 --> 00:21:07.223
You think I wanted to blow my hand off?

464
00:21:07.224 --> 00:21:08.891
Then you need to listen to me
when I tell you something.

465
00:21:08.892 --> 00:21:11.269
- You're not my mom.
- You think I want to be your mom?

466
00:21:11.270 --> 00:21:13.522
Chantal. why don't we take a step outside?

467
00:21:17.985 --> 00:21:20.695
So I know that this can be very stressful.

468
00:21:20.696 --> 00:21:22.697
Yeah. he almost lost
his hand being stupid.

469
00:21:22.698 --> 00:21:24.699
- He's a really sweet kid.
- He used to be.

470
00:21:24.700 --> 00:21:26.743
We also found something in his blood work.

471
00:21:27.578 --> 00:21:30.581
- What?
- He has a blood alcohol of 0.08.

472
00:21:32.207 --> 00:21:33.583
What. he was drunk?

473
00:21:33.584 --> 00:21:35.251
Are you fucking kidding me?

474
00:21:35.252 --> 00:21:37.880
- Does he drink regularly?
- No.

475
00:21:39.381 --> 00:21:40.923
I don't know.

476
00:21:40.924 --> 00:21:44.719
The boys at our apartment complex
are a really bad influence.

477
00:21:44.720 --> 00:21:47.722
- I mean. he's only 12.
- That is what concerns us.

478
00:21:47.723 --> 00:21:51.183
A positive blood alcohol immediately
triggers a social service consult.

479
00:21:51.184 --> 00:21:52.894
They gonna take my brother away from me?

480
00:21:52.895 --> 00:21:55.313
It's an evaluation to determine
if the injury and the drinking

481
00:21:55.314 --> 00:21:57.940
- is cause for some kind of intervention.
- I won't let you separate us.

482
00:21:57.941 --> 00:21:59.526
- We are required to...
- No!

483
00:22:09.786 --> 00:22:11.162
58-year-old woman with nausea.

484
00:22:11.163 --> 00:22:13.664
vomited once after eating
warm potato salad at a barbecue.

485
00:22:13.665 --> 00:22:14.665
Well-hydrated.

486
00:22:14.666 --> 00:22:17.627
Abdomen's pretty benign. just a little
distended with mild tenderness.

487
00:22:17.628 --> 00:22:19.837
History of constipation.
I give her Zofran.

488
00:22:19.838 --> 00:22:21.631
Labs and abdominal series pending.

489
00:22:21.632 --> 00:22:23.841
- Okay. let's take a look.
- Okay.

490
00:22:23.842 --> 00:22:25.176
Hi. Mrs. Burns.

491
00:22:25.177 --> 00:22:27.054
This is Dr. Whitaker.
How are you feeling?

492
00:22:28.055 --> 00:22:29.056
Mrs. Burns?

493
00:22:30.098 --> 00:22:32.308
Mrs. Burns. can you open your eyes for me?

494
00:22:32.309 --> 00:22:33.768
She was awake and alert
last time I saw her.

495
00:22:33.769 --> 00:22:36.896
Okay. feels warm. thready pulse.

496
00:22:36.897 --> 00:22:38.731
Abdomen's more distended than before.

497
00:22:38.732 --> 00:22:40.858
Okay. agonal respirations.

498
00:22:40.859 --> 00:22:42.818
- She's hardly breathing.
- It's kind of rigid.

499
00:22:42.819 --> 00:22:46.030
Yeah. yeah. Perlah. we need a crash cart.
Can you call respiratory?

500
00:22:46.031 --> 00:22:48.574
- Pull the bed out for intubation. please.
- Yeah.

501
00:22:48.575 --> 00:22:50.077
I can give you guys some room.

502
00:22:51.078 --> 00:22:52.370
- Okay.
- What's up?

503
00:22:52.371 --> 00:22:54.997
Hypotensive. acute abdomen.
She needs an airway.

504
00:22:54.998 --> 00:22:57.083
- I'll find the GlideScope.
- No time for that.

505
00:22:57.084 --> 00:22:58.459
We've got direct on the crash cart.

506
00:22:58.460 --> 00:23:00.211
- Whitaker. you're up.
- I haven't done many directs.

507
00:23:00.212 --> 00:23:01.379
Well. then you need to do more.

508
00:23:01.380 --> 00:23:03.881
- Induction meds?
- 100 ketamine. 80 of raw.

509
00:23:03.882 --> 00:23:05.634
Javadi. what's the story?

510
00:23:06.551 --> 00:23:09.471
Presented with mild abdominal pain.
took a turn for the worse.

511
00:23:11.431 --> 00:23:14.058
A-fib 122. BP 98 and systolic.

512
00:23:14.059 --> 00:23:15.810
Okay. let's bolus another 500 cc's.

513
00:23:15.811 --> 00:23:18.062
- We shocking her?
- Maybe. After intubation.

514
00:23:18.063 --> 00:23:19.689
Check your light. Check your balloon.

515
00:23:19.690 --> 00:23:21.816
Javadi. AP pads in case
we need to cardiovert.

516
00:23:21.817 --> 00:23:24.151
Normal EKG at triage. She wasn't in A-fib.

517
00:23:24.152 --> 00:23:26.487
Stress from her condition
probably put her there.

518
00:23:26.488 --> 00:23:27.905
Good? Let's roll her.

519
00:23:27.906 --> 00:23:29.740
- Do we have any labs back?
- I don't think so.

520
00:23:29.741 --> 00:23:32.493
- What else do we need?
- Blood cultures.

521
00:23:32.494 --> 00:23:34.955
Lactate. 2 liters LR. 3.375 pip-tazo.

522
00:23:35.831 --> 00:23:37.916
Okay. she's loose.
Go ahead. Whitaker. Take a look.

523
00:23:38.542 --> 00:23:39.710
Okay.

524
00:23:46.550 --> 00:23:49.343
Hi. I'm Dr. Santos.
This is student doctor Kwon.

525
00:23:49.344 --> 00:23:52.763
- How are you doing after the mist?
- Better than I was an hour ago.

526
00:23:52.764 --> 00:23:55.517
Okay. we are going to check your vitals.

527
00:23:57.728 --> 00:24:02.064
Temp is 100.2. and heart rate is 96.

528
00:24:02.065 --> 00:24:05.444
Okay. down from 101.5 and 120.
Very good.

529
00:24:06.278 --> 00:24:08.446
You were out in the heat in that costume?

530
00:24:08.447 --> 00:24:11.365
Yeah. with about 18.000 of my friends.

531
00:24:11.366 --> 00:24:12.617
Were you at Anthrocon?

532
00:24:13.744 --> 00:24:16.662
- What's that?
- Pittsburgh's annual furry convention.

533
00:24:16.663 --> 00:24:17.956
I go every year.

534
00:24:18.749 --> 00:24:19.708
Ever been?

535
00:24:20.751 --> 00:24:22.377
It's not really my scene.

536
00:24:23.253 --> 00:24:27.673
Yeah. furries get a bad rap. but there are
great people in the community...

537
00:24:27.674 --> 00:24:31.302
creative. welcoming. funny.

538
00:24:31.303 --> 00:24:33.846
I actually met my girlfriend
at last year's convention.

539
00:24:33.847 --> 00:24:35.556
Oh. that's cute.

540
00:24:35.557 --> 00:24:38.476
She gave me hope after struggling
on the dating apps.

541
00:24:38.477 --> 00:24:41.479
Nice to hear that meeting people
in real life still works.

542
00:24:41.480 --> 00:24:43.774
Wouldn't recommend it. especially at work.

543
00:24:44.900 --> 00:24:46.902
You should come to Anthrocon this weekend.

544
00:24:47.944 --> 00:24:50.321
Doesn't she need a fur suit for that?

545
00:24:50.322 --> 00:24:51.990
I think you'd make a good dragon.

546
00:24:56.078 --> 00:24:57.411
I'm in.

547
00:24:57.412 --> 00:24:58.830
Balloon up.

548
00:24:59.998 --> 00:25:01.541
Yep. bag her.

549
00:25:02.209 --> 00:25:03.209
Okay.

550
00:25:03.210 --> 00:25:05.961
- That was harder without video.
- We won't always have video.

551
00:25:05.962 --> 00:25:08.547
A-fib now at 152.
Blood pressure's down to 76 over 44.

552
00:25:08.548 --> 00:25:12.594
Okay. Javadi. sync mode.
Javadi. sync mode. 200. please.

553
00:25:13.428 --> 00:25:15.221
Good end tidal waveform.

554
00:25:15.222 --> 00:25:17.808
Good breath sounds bilaterally.

555
00:25:19.017 --> 00:25:21.228
- Charged for cardioversion.
- Everyone. clear.

556
00:25:25.607 --> 00:25:27.442
Normal sinus. Normal radial pulse.

557
00:25:29.611 --> 00:25:32.447
Good. Keep the fluids going.
Let's see what labs are back on her.

558
00:25:35.033 --> 00:25:36.367
Nice.

559
00:25:36.368 --> 00:25:37.828
Very nice.

560
00:25:39.079 --> 00:25:42.039
- What did you order?
- CBC. ER chem panel.

561
00:25:42.040 --> 00:25:44.625
- Something should be back.
- Fax machine ran out of toner.

562
00:25:44.626 --> 00:25:47.253
- Check the chart.
- There is no chart in slot 22.

563
00:25:47.254 --> 00:25:48.839
Check the orders rack.

564
00:25:49.840 --> 00:25:51.298
Nothing here either.

565
00:25:51.299 --> 00:25:53.260
Where's the chart for Claire Burns?

566
00:25:55.720 --> 00:25:58.722
Claire Burns. order slip.
Never drawn. never sent off to the lab.

567
00:25:58.723 --> 00:26:00.474
That's cause the patient
wasn't on the board.

568
00:26:00.475 --> 00:26:01.767
Nurses are working zones.

569
00:26:01.768 --> 00:26:03.978
If the patient's not
on the board. they don't exist.

570
00:26:03.979 --> 00:26:06.564
- So they didn't shoot her X-ray?
- X-ray downtime box is empty.

571
00:26:06.565 --> 00:26:08.983
- That means it was done.
- Then it's on the portable machine.

572
00:26:08.984 --> 00:26:11.777
Last I saw. it was headed north.

573
00:26:11.778 --> 00:26:13.988
- Thanks. Dana.
- Yep.

574
00:26:13.989 --> 00:26:16.782
- Hey. Kenny. can you wait up a sec?
- If you need an X-ray. write the order.

575
00:26:16.783 --> 00:26:18.033
Fill out a downtime.

576
00:26:18.034 --> 00:26:20.786
- Did you shoot a KUB in South 22?
- No. Maybe another tech did?

577
00:26:20.787 --> 00:26:23.999
Okay. can you flick through the films.
look for a patient... Burns?

578
00:26:28.670 --> 00:26:31.005
- Oh. shit.
- Oh. that is a classic sigmoid volvulus.

579
00:26:31.006 --> 00:26:32.798
- Peritoneal signs.
- Okay. call the OR.

580
00:26:32.799 --> 00:26:34.551
She's going to need surgery ASAP.

581
00:26:43.518 --> 00:26:45.561
Urine shows three plus blood.

582
00:26:45.562 --> 00:26:46.688
No surprise.

583
00:26:47.564 --> 00:26:51.192
BUN and creatinine are normal.
No evidence of renal insufficiency.

584
00:26:51.193 --> 00:26:52.943
I got a good look at the left kidney...

585
00:26:52.944 --> 00:26:56.864
mild hydronephrosis consistent
with ureteral column.

586
00:26:56.865 --> 00:26:59.200
- How was the rest of the ultrasound?
- Normal.

587
00:26:59.201 --> 00:27:02.286
Pain improved after 15 ketorolac IM.

588
00:27:02.287 --> 00:27:04.539
Now you can give another 15 and observe.

589
00:27:07.167 --> 00:27:09.544
Just need you to cosign my order.

590
00:27:11.755 --> 00:27:13.464
Thank you.

591
00:27:13.465 --> 00:27:15.549
Something on your mind?

592
00:27:15.550 --> 00:27:18.177
Yeah. I saw this regular an hour ago.

593
00:27:18.178 --> 00:27:20.054
He's in his 60s. fakes an ailment

594
00:27:20.055 --> 00:27:22.473
so he can come in to chat
every now and then

595
00:27:22.474 --> 00:27:24.475
because he's really lonely.

596
00:27:24.476 --> 00:27:26.477
You sure he just doesn't have
a crush on you?

597
00:27:26.478 --> 00:27:29.063
Maybe. but it got me thinking
about my mom.

598
00:27:29.064 --> 00:27:31.149
She's probably just been lonely.

599
00:27:31.858 --> 00:27:32.859
Yeah.

600
00:27:34.027 --> 00:27:38.072
You know. I haven't really dated
since my divorce.

601
00:27:38.073 --> 00:27:40.866
Medical school. my kid. residency.

602
00:27:40.867 --> 00:27:43.077
And now I'm feeling finally kind of ready.

603
00:27:43.078 --> 00:27:46.497
I was waiting until I got back to Jersey
to work on finding a relationship.

604
00:27:46.498 --> 00:27:48.415
and now that's out the window.

605
00:27:48.416 --> 00:27:50.584
Maybe I waited too long.

606
00:27:50.585 --> 00:27:51.752
For what?

607
00:27:51.753 --> 00:27:52.963
Do you hear that?

608
00:27:53.630 --> 00:27:57.759
That painful. lonely silence
is the sound of my eggs dying.

609
00:28:01.972 --> 00:28:04.014
So the rash in North 3
has been discharged.

610
00:28:04.015 --> 00:28:06.892
The Tasered law student in Central 10
has gone up to psych.

611
00:28:06.893 --> 00:28:09.019
The eye stroke is now in the ICU.

612
00:28:09.020 --> 00:28:12.314
And the tongue laceration in South 15
is sobering up before we discharge.

613
00:28:12.315 --> 00:28:14.108
which better be soon
because we need the room.

614
00:28:14.109 --> 00:28:16.694
Okay. I'll grab a med student
and get more patients moving out.

615
00:28:16.695 --> 00:28:19.363
You're not fazed by any of this chaos?

616
00:28:19.364 --> 00:28:21.115
What a fucking mess.

617
00:28:21.116 --> 00:28:22.993
Jesus Christ. we need you.

618
00:28:24.202 --> 00:28:27.371
Monica Peters. this is our new
attending. Dr. Al-Hashimi.

619
00:28:27.372 --> 00:28:29.331
- Welcome.
- Thank you.

620
00:28:29.332 --> 00:28:31.542
Monica's a retired clerk.
best of the best.

621
00:28:31.543 --> 00:28:33.335
She was kind enough
to come in on a holiday

622
00:28:33.336 --> 00:28:34.712
and help get us back into shape.

623
00:28:34.713 --> 00:28:36.338
Laid off by the digital revolution.

624
00:28:36.339 --> 00:28:37.715
- not retired.
- Okay.

625
00:28:37.716 --> 00:28:40.551
And how's all this digital shit
working out for you now?

626
00:28:40.552 --> 00:28:43.137
- Not so good.
- Exactly.

627
00:28:43.138 --> 00:28:46.140
All right. then. who's handling
the charts and the orders?

628
00:28:46.141 --> 00:28:47.474
That's us. right here.

629
00:28:47.475 --> 00:28:49.351
How long have you been clerks?

630
00:28:49.352 --> 00:28:51.687
Just today. We're medical assistants.

631
00:28:51.688 --> 00:28:54.732
Then get out of my space and go do
something you know how to do.

632
00:28:54.733 --> 00:28:58.360
And no personal calls.
Red phones are for emergencies only.

633
00:28:58.361 --> 00:29:01.488
- This is a hospital. for God's sake.
- I'll call you back.

634
00:29:01.489 --> 00:29:03.157
- Got a gumband?
- Yeah.

635
00:29:03.158 --> 00:29:06.368
Hi. I'm Makedah from admin and records.
I have a new badge for a Dr. Whitaker.

636
00:29:06.369 --> 00:29:08.579
Yeah. I'll get that to him.

637
00:29:08.580 --> 00:29:09.997
Heard you all need extra runners?

638
00:29:09.998 --> 00:29:12.374
- Perfect timing.
- How fast can you move?

639
00:29:12.375 --> 00:29:14.126
- I run marathons.
- Great.

640
00:29:14.127 --> 00:29:17.004
Grab the blood samples and the bin
and get them up to the lab.

641
00:29:17.005 --> 00:29:19.340
I want a lab run every 15 minutes.

642
00:29:19.341 --> 00:29:20.425
Got it.

643
00:29:26.181 --> 00:29:28.390
I work at a shoe store in Oakland.

644
00:29:28.391 --> 00:29:31.769
- Full-time and you're in school?
- Yes. and. yes.

645
00:29:31.770 --> 00:29:33.479
Allegheny Community.

646
00:29:33.480 --> 00:29:35.981
Does Jude go to summer school or camp

647
00:29:35.982 --> 00:29:38.568
while you're at work or school?

648
00:29:40.070 --> 00:29:41.779
Can't afford it.

649
00:29:41.780 --> 00:29:43.405
Are there any other family members

650
00:29:43.406 --> 00:29:45.824
that could help with his care
when you're not available?

651
00:29:45.825 --> 00:29:46.910
No.

652
00:29:50.413 --> 00:29:53.833
Chantal. we want to help you.
but we can't help if you won't talk to us.

653
00:29:54.501 --> 00:29:57.337
What. you're gonna take Jude away
and put him in foster care?

654
00:29:58.296 --> 00:30:00.715
I promised my parents
that would never happen.

655
00:30:01.299 --> 00:30:03.425
Did your parents pass away?

656
00:30:03.426 --> 00:30:04.968
Nope.

657
00:30:04.969 --> 00:30:06.513
What happened to them?

658
00:30:13.311 --> 00:30:16.439
My parents were deported
to Haiti nine months ago.

659
00:30:19.067 --> 00:30:22.904
They went in for their immigration hearing
and were detained.

660
00:30:24.531 --> 00:30:26.240
I was a sophomore at Ithaca.

661
00:30:26.241 --> 00:30:28.284
I had to move back home
to take care of my brother.

662
00:30:30.036 --> 00:30:31.037
I'm sorry.

663
00:30:31.913 --> 00:30:35.125
It was either that. or he moved
back to Haiti with them.

664
00:30:36.334 --> 00:30:37.919
He's never been there.

665
00:30:38.878 --> 00:30:41.005
We were both born here.

666
00:30:43.925 --> 00:30:47.261
My mom was so excited
when I got into college.

667
00:30:47.262 --> 00:30:49.388
She worked so hard

668
00:30:49.389 --> 00:30:52.349
to save up and pay my tuition.

669
00:30:52.350 --> 00:30:56.020
And now all she wants
is for my brother to finish high school.

670
00:30:58.773 --> 00:31:02.569
Man. being a big sister's a lot easier
than being a surrogate mom.

671
00:31:05.447 --> 00:31:08.741
Just give us a moment. please.
and I'll come grab you when we're done.

672
00:31:13.288 --> 00:31:15.747
Do we really need to get
family services involved?

673
00:31:15.748 --> 00:31:17.749
You wanted to get
them involved this morning

674
00:31:17.750 --> 00:31:19.377
with your eight-year-old ITP patient.

675
00:31:20.044 --> 00:31:22.713
That's different. Abuse trumps neglect.

676
00:31:22.714 --> 00:31:25.383
We can't separate her from her brother.
It's not right.

677
00:31:25.925 --> 00:31:27.802
A lot of what happens
to people around here isn't right.

678
00:31:33.808 --> 00:31:36.894
McKay. patient's complaining of pain.

679
00:31:36.895 --> 00:31:37.979
Yeah.

680
00:31:39.522 --> 00:31:43.984
- Hey. Amaya. What's going on?
- Oh. it really fucking hurts again.

681
00:31:43.985 --> 00:31:46.111
Hey. Jesse. can you grab Whitaker?

682
00:31:46.112 --> 00:31:48.322
- When did it get bad?
- Two minutes ago.

683
00:31:48.323 --> 00:31:50.741
Giving you some morphine
to take the edge off.

684
00:31:50.742 --> 00:31:54.119
- How severe. 1 to 10?
- 12. It's way worse.

685
00:31:54.120 --> 00:31:55.120
Okay.

686
00:31:55.121 --> 00:31:58.123
Hey. Amaya. the meds will kick in.
and we'll get you back on the foot rest

687
00:31:58.124 --> 00:32:00.084
to see what's going on. okay?

688
00:32:06.007 --> 00:32:08.800
I had to call her husband
in New York to get consent.

689
00:32:08.801 --> 00:32:09.885
Okay.

690
00:32:09.886 --> 00:32:11.846
Dr. Shamsi will be operating.

691
00:32:12.388 --> 00:32:15.016
If she presented with peritoneal signs.
why wasn't I called?

692
00:32:15.975 --> 00:32:18.602
There was a delayed presentation.

693
00:32:18.603 --> 00:32:21.355
The X-ray was shot an hour ago.
Why didn't anybody read it?

694
00:32:21.356 --> 00:32:23.357
There was confusion
with the digital systems down.

695
00:32:23.358 --> 00:32:25.526
It wasn't read.
We didn't get a report.

696
00:32:25.527 --> 00:32:29.821
An hour ago. I could have fixed this
in 60 seconds with a rectal tube.

697
00:32:29.822 --> 00:32:31.574
Now she needs major surgery.

698
00:32:32.242 --> 00:32:34.284
- I'm sorry.
- Not good enough. nepo baby.

699
00:32:34.285 --> 00:32:35.494
You fucked up.

700
00:32:35.495 --> 00:32:37.956
Don't trust anything or anybody else
when the system's down.

701
00:32:39.874 --> 00:32:43.294
With all the chaos.
she just fell through the cracks.

702
00:32:45.088 --> 00:32:46.881
She almost died.

703
00:32:48.258 --> 00:32:49.967
I could have killed her.

704
00:32:49.968 --> 00:32:51.176
- Whitaker.
- No...

705
00:32:51.177 --> 00:32:53.054
McKay needs you in Central 11.

706
00:32:54.097 --> 00:32:57.475
We caught it in time.
We won't let it happen again. okay?

707
00:33:10.071 --> 00:33:12.490
Oh. Princess is looking for you.

708
00:33:13.533 --> 00:33:15.409
She said something
about Monica under her breath.

709
00:33:15.410 --> 00:33:18.704
- but I couldn't make it out.
- Okay. I'll be back in a sec.

710
00:33:18.705 --> 00:33:20.498
Hey. Hey.

711
00:33:21.916 --> 00:33:24.085
You did good
with that sexual-assault victim.

712
00:33:25.336 --> 00:33:27.337
You were amazing with her.

713
00:33:27.338 --> 00:33:29.214
We do what we can to provide the best care

714
00:33:29.215 --> 00:33:32.093
to traumatized people
in their darkest days.

715
00:33:33.428 --> 00:33:36.221
What'd you talk to her about
when you took her out on the walk?

716
00:33:36.222 --> 00:33:37.515
I...

717
00:33:38.933 --> 00:33:40.642
told her there might be a time
in the future

718
00:33:40.643 --> 00:33:44.314
when she changes her mind.
wants to press charges.

719
00:33:45.732 --> 00:33:48.275
It's better to have
the option to do it than not.

720
00:33:48.276 --> 00:33:49.527
Smart.

721
00:33:52.697 --> 00:33:54.239
Is every day like this?

722
00:33:54.240 --> 00:33:57.327
Minus the cyberattacks. yeah.

723
00:33:58.453 --> 00:34:02.123
But you're only a few hours away
from being done with your first of many.

724
00:34:03.041 --> 00:34:04.459
Be proud of that.

725
00:34:11.549 --> 00:34:13.675
You're gonna want to be on a soft diet.

726
00:34:13.676 --> 00:34:16.637
so things like mashed potatoes.

727
00:34:16.638 --> 00:34:19.056
soup. mac and cheese are good.

728
00:34:19.057 --> 00:34:21.475
I was gonna make your favorite
three-bean dip tonight.

729
00:34:21.476 --> 00:34:24.771
- Bitch. that is so nice.
- See. I am nice.

730
00:34:25.563 --> 00:34:27.481
Could she have that?

731
00:34:27.482 --> 00:34:30.192
Yeah. Yeah. yeah.
if you eat it with a spoon

732
00:34:30.193 --> 00:34:31.902
rather than anything. like. crunchy

733
00:34:31.903 --> 00:34:33.571
that could work its way
into the laceration.

734
00:34:34.572 --> 00:34:36.783
So she'll need to be spoon-fed?

735
00:34:38.368 --> 00:34:39.910
Antibiotics three times a day.

736
00:34:39.911 --> 00:34:42.245
Come back here in two days
for a wound check.

737
00:34:42.246 --> 00:34:43.998
See you then. Doctor.

738
00:34:46.167 --> 00:34:48.795
Checking blood flow to the ovary.

739
00:34:53.508 --> 00:34:56.301
- Something wrong?
- Intermittent torsion.

740
00:34:56.302 --> 00:34:57.719
What's that?

741
00:34:57.720 --> 00:34:59.430
I'm coming out now.

742
00:35:00.515 --> 00:35:01.932
We will slide you back.

743
00:35:01.933 --> 00:35:03.517
Thanks.

744
00:35:03.518 --> 00:35:07.938
Your ovary is twisting
and cutting off the blood supply.

745
00:35:07.939 --> 00:35:10.315
That's what's been causing your pain.

746
00:35:10.316 --> 00:35:13.610
You said the blood supply was fine before.

747
00:35:13.611 --> 00:35:16.197
Sometimes the ovary can twist randomly.

748
00:35:17.198 --> 00:35:20.201
In those cases. the pain can come and go.

749
00:35:21.202 --> 00:35:23.745
- Can you fix it?
- With surgery.

750
00:35:23.746 --> 00:35:25.080
"Surgery"?

751
00:35:25.081 --> 00:35:26.957
The ovary needs to be untwisted

752
00:35:26.958 --> 00:35:29.960
and tacked down with a stitch
so this doesn't happen again.

753
00:35:29.961 --> 00:35:32.630
If we can get you upstairs quickly.
we can save it.

754
00:35:33.381 --> 00:35:35.216
I could lose my ovary?

755
00:35:36.426 --> 00:35:38.427
Will I still be able to have a baby?

756
00:35:38.428 --> 00:35:39.970
This shouldn't be an issue in the future.

757
00:35:39.971 --> 00:35:43.765
Dr. McKay made the right call
to keep you in the ER for observation

758
00:35:43.766 --> 00:35:45.893
so we could catch it if the pain returned.

759
00:35:47.562 --> 00:35:49.354
Thank you.

760
00:35:49.355 --> 00:35:50.982
- I'll call GYN.
- Yeah.

761
00:35:53.776 --> 00:35:55.694
Hey. welcome back.
How was the trip?

762
00:35:55.695 --> 00:35:57.738
Smooth sailing.
Presby's pretty nice.

763
00:35:57.739 --> 00:36:00.450
I might have to pick up
some day shifts over there.

764
00:36:01.075 --> 00:36:02.492
<i>Dr. Abbot's funny.</i>

765
00:36:02.493 --> 00:36:03.994
Trust me. his charm wears off.

766
00:36:03.995 --> 00:36:06.079
- No. it doesn't.
- He's not sedated?

767
00:36:06.080 --> 00:36:08.373
I gave him Versed for the CT scan
on the ride back.

768
00:36:08.374 --> 00:36:10.333
but I figured he'd need to be awake
and alert

769
00:36:10.334 --> 00:36:11.668
- to give consent.
- "Consent"?

770
00:36:11.669 --> 00:36:13.253
Yep. We're going to get you settled.

771
00:36:13.254 --> 00:36:14.796
Why don't you page Garcia to come down?

772
00:36:14.797 --> 00:36:16.506
- Dr. Robby.
- You got this?

773
00:36:16.507 --> 00:36:18.468
- You know I got it.
- Yep.

774
00:36:19.093 --> 00:36:20.678
All right. Howard.

775
00:36:21.387 --> 00:36:24.931
Hey. I want to debrief with you later
on your sigmoid volvulus patient.

776
00:36:24.932 --> 00:36:26.725
I finished
with your fireworks kid's sister.

777
00:36:26.726 --> 00:36:27.642
And?

778
00:36:27.643 --> 00:36:29.352
She's a responsible
young woman and a good guardian to Jude.

779
00:36:29.353 --> 00:36:31.980
There is no reason to get
family services involved today.

780
00:36:31.981 --> 00:36:33.064
That's good.

781
00:36:33.065 --> 00:36:34.816
Because he's in the hospital for surgery.

782
00:36:34.817 --> 00:36:36.610
but they will most likely make
a home visit next week

783
00:36:36.611 --> 00:36:39.821
to evaluate the safety of their apartment
and the care that Chantal can provide.

784
00:36:39.822 --> 00:36:41.198
along with her other responsibilities.

785
00:36:41.199 --> 00:36:42.741
And then what? They take Jude?

786
00:36:42.742 --> 00:36:45.035
In my experience.
they'll make the same assessment I did.

787
00:36:45.036 --> 00:36:46.537
They don't like
to separate siblings.

788
00:36:47.622 --> 00:36:48.955
Anything else we can do for 'em?

789
00:36:48.956 --> 00:36:51.333
I'll get some resources together
for Chantal...

790
00:36:51.334 --> 00:36:52.834
summer after-school programs.

791
00:36:52.835 --> 00:36:55.629
But there might come a point when he'd be
better off with his parents in Haiti.

792
00:36:55.630 --> 00:36:58.215
- His parents want him to stay here.
- It's what's best for the child.

793
00:36:58.216 --> 00:37:00.050
- Says who?
- Dr. Santos.

794
00:37:00.051 --> 00:37:01.302
Come on.

795
00:37:03.888 --> 00:37:06.139
Welcome back. Mr. Knox.
What did we discover?

796
00:37:06.140 --> 00:37:08.725
Diverticular abscess
that progressed to perforation.

797
00:37:08.726 --> 00:37:10.685
now with free air under the diaphragm.

798
00:37:10.686 --> 00:37:12.062
<i>In English. please?</i>

799
00:37:12.063 --> 00:37:15.899
There's a small hole in the colon
that's spilling bacteria into the abdomen.

800
00:37:15.900 --> 00:37:19.070
You're likely to develop
peritonitis and sepsis.

801
00:37:20.321 --> 00:37:22.447
<i>- How bad?</i>
- You need surgery now.

802
00:37:22.448 --> 00:37:24.492
You have a 100% chance
of death without it.

803
00:37:26.661 --> 00:37:27.954
<i>With it?</i>

804
00:37:30.456 --> 00:37:32.166
50% chance.

805
00:37:35.336 --> 00:37:38.463
<i>- I could die?</i>
- Yes. but we're very good at what we do.

806
00:37:38.464 --> 00:37:41.342
That is what the consent is for.

807
00:37:41.968 --> 00:37:43.593
<i>What about my sister?</i>

808
00:37:43.594 --> 00:37:46.638
We found her.
She'd like to speak with you.

809
00:37:46.639 --> 00:37:50.517
We don't have time for that.
Any delay increases your mortality risks.

810
00:37:50.518 --> 00:37:52.979
<i>I want to talk to my sister first.</i>

811
00:37:56.816 --> 00:37:59.151
We're gonna make that happen for you.

812
00:37:59.902 --> 00:38:02.904
I'll have them prep an OR.
but make it fast. very fast.

813
00:38:02.905 --> 00:38:05.032
Yeah. We're on the move again. Howard.

814
00:38:20.590 --> 00:38:21.591
Hey.

815
00:38:24.385 --> 00:38:26.387
The ice cream party over?

816
00:38:28.431 --> 00:38:29.599
Yes.

817
00:38:30.600 --> 00:38:32.393
Do you need anything?

818
00:38:35.605 --> 00:38:37.356
A time machine.

819
00:38:41.527 --> 00:38:43.404
That'd be nice. wouldn't it?

820
00:38:48.117 --> 00:38:51.162
I don't even know what hurts more...

821
00:38:51.829 --> 00:38:53.831
the cancer or...

822
00:38:56.626 --> 00:38:59.712
knowing I'm never gonna see
my sons grow up.

823
00:39:02.381 --> 00:39:04.508
It feels like a cruel joke.

824
00:39:06.302 --> 00:39:10.847
Why give me children and a husband I adore

825
00:39:10.848 --> 00:39:13.059
if you're just gonna
take them away from me?

826
00:39:15.061 --> 00:39:18.064
For what? Fucking lung cancer.

827
00:39:21.400 --> 00:39:23.069
I didn't even smoke.

828
00:39:31.452 --> 00:39:33.204
Do you believe in God?

829
00:39:35.748 --> 00:39:37.708
I like the concept.

830
00:39:41.879 --> 00:39:43.881
I'm sure you've seen a lot of death.

831
00:39:45.257 --> 00:39:47.093
I have seen my share.

832
00:39:50.096 --> 00:39:51.889
Any advice?

833
00:39:57.478 --> 00:39:59.897
I've never died before.

834
00:40:09.740 --> 00:40:11.616
Hey. sorry. We're outside.

835
00:40:11.617 --> 00:40:16.288
There's no cell service inside right now.
but here he is.

836
00:40:18.708 --> 00:40:21.711
<i>Oh. my God. Are you all right?</i>

837
00:40:23.838 --> 00:40:26.507
<i>Been better. You look beautiful.</i>

838
00:40:27.925 --> 00:40:29.551
<i>Thank you.</i>

839
00:40:29.552 --> 00:40:31.554
<i>You're not looking so hot.</i>

840
00:40:33.973 --> 00:40:35.933
<i>Thank you for calling back.</i>

841
00:40:38.728 --> 00:40:40.146
<i>Of course.</i>

842
00:40:40.730 --> 00:40:43.190
<i>I'm sorry that it's been this long.</i>

843
00:40:43.733 --> 00:40:46.152
<i>All the stuff with Dad
and the drinking. I...</i>

844
00:40:47.361 --> 00:40:49.238
<i>I had to do what was best
for me and Tommy.</i>

845
00:40:50.406 --> 00:40:51.949
<i>How is Tommy?</i>

846
00:40:52.908 --> 00:40:56.786
<i>Starting his junior year
in high school next month.</i>

847
00:40:56.787 --> 00:40:59.540
<i>16 and already has a girlfriend.</i>

848
00:41:02.251 --> 00:41:04.170
<i>Takes after his uncle.</i>

849
00:41:06.589 --> 00:41:10.718
<i>Maybe we can make a plan for you
to see each other over the holidays.</i>

850
00:41:15.181 --> 00:41:16.515
<i>I'd love that.</i>

851
00:41:18.559 --> 00:41:20.269
<i>Is the doctor there?</i>

852
00:41:22.354 --> 00:41:23.480
Hi. I'm Dr. Abbot.

853
00:41:23.481 --> 00:41:25.231
<i>Can you call me
when he gets out of surgery?</i>

854
00:41:25.232 --> 00:41:27.317
Of course. but right now we need to get
him up to the OR.

855
00:41:27.318 --> 00:41:28.652
<i>I understand. Thanks.</i>

856
00:41:29.195 --> 00:41:30.988
<i>Talk to you soon. Howard.</i>

857
00:41:33.574 --> 00:41:35.659
<i>Oh. I forgot to tell him I love him.</i>

858
00:41:36.827 --> 00:41:38.996
Oh. wow. Monica?

859
00:41:39.997 --> 00:41:42.416
- Welcome back.
- Robinavitch.

860
00:41:43.334 --> 00:41:46.002
- Two for the lab. three for CT.
- I'll take those.

861
00:41:46.003 --> 00:41:48.214
- They need me upstairs.
- On it for CT.

862
00:41:48.839 --> 00:41:51.508
- You run a tight ship.
- Well. it's a work in progress.

863
00:41:51.509 --> 00:41:53.927
- Is he going up?
- Yeah.

864
00:41:53.928 --> 00:41:55.805
He's a good guy.

865
00:41:57.598 --> 00:41:59.809
Our surgeons will get him through.

866
00:42:04.605 --> 00:42:05.815
I like her.

867
00:42:06.816 --> 00:42:08.483
More than me?

868
00:42:08.484 --> 00:42:10.236
Only time will tell.

869
00:42:11.028 --> 00:42:13.154
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

870
00:42:13.155 --> 00:42:15.448
She has good command
of staff and procedures.

871
00:42:15.449 --> 00:42:18.701
I think you're leaving your day shift
in very capable hands.

872
00:42:18.702 --> 00:42:20.203
I hope so.

873
00:42:20.204 --> 00:42:22.372
All right. I'm out of here. man.

874
00:42:22.373 --> 00:42:24.708
I got to be back
in a few hours for my shift.

875
00:42:25.376 --> 00:42:27.169
Well. hey. if I don't see you...

876
00:42:27.837 --> 00:42:29.463
You're really doing this still?

877
00:42:30.256 --> 00:42:32.966
I don't think I can remember the last time
you took three days off in a row.

878
00:42:32.967 --> 00:42:35.052
I've taken a vacation before.

879
00:42:36.303 --> 00:42:37.847
Name the last one.

880
00:42:40.891 --> 00:42:42.268
Point taken.

881
00:42:43.644 --> 00:42:46.480
It's gonna be a lot of time
to self-reflect.

882
00:42:48.858 --> 00:42:50.276
You sure you can handle that?

883
00:42:53.279 --> 00:42:54.488
Okay.

884
00:42:55.322 --> 00:42:57.407
You just make sure you come back.

885
00:42:57.408 --> 00:43:00.077
And if it gets dark. you call me.

886
00:43:01.662 --> 00:43:02.830
You listening?

887
00:43:08.085 --> 00:43:10.211
So the ankle's negative for fracture.

888
00:43:10.212 --> 00:43:11.630
Wait. go back to the ankle.

889
00:43:12.506 --> 00:43:14.132
You see the normal mortise?

890
00:43:14.133 --> 00:43:17.218
Yeah. but the tibiofibular clear space
looks enlarged.

891
00:43:17.219 --> 00:43:20.305
and the tibiofibular overlap
seems reduced.

892
00:43:20.306 --> 00:43:21.682
Maybe a little.

893
00:43:23.767 --> 00:43:26.769
8 millimeters. 3 millimeters.

894
00:43:26.770 --> 00:43:29.189
Seems like a tear
in the syndesmotic ligaments.

895
00:43:29.190 --> 00:43:31.024
Doesn't that need surgical fixation?

896
00:43:31.025 --> 00:43:34.111
They do. I can request an MRI.

897
00:43:35.529 --> 00:43:37.363
Have you done
a radiology clerkship before?

898
00:43:37.364 --> 00:43:40.117
No. I'm just that good.

899
00:43:43.120 --> 00:43:44.705
I'm good at things. too.

900
00:43:55.966 --> 00:43:59.553
Really great work earlier today. Doctor.

901
00:44:03.557 --> 00:44:04.891
Oh. wow.

902
00:44:04.892 --> 00:44:08.478
- You can just call me Whitaker.
- Not a chance. You earned that.

903
00:44:08.479 --> 00:44:10.981
I'm proud of you. We all are.

904
00:44:11.815 --> 00:44:12.857
Thank you.

905
00:44:12.858 --> 00:44:15.485
- Busy day.
- Oh. yeah.

906
00:44:15.486 --> 00:44:18.488
So you're a very empathetic soul.

907
00:44:18.489 --> 00:44:20.531
- Yeah. I'd like to think...
- I'm not finished yet.

908
00:44:20.532 --> 00:44:22.867
And you want to be there
for all your patients.

909
00:44:22.868 --> 00:44:23.994
Don't you?

910
00:44:24.745 --> 00:44:26.663
- Sorry.
- So this relationship that you're having

911
00:44:26.664 --> 00:44:29.874
with this woman.
the widow of the burn victim

912
00:44:29.875 --> 00:44:32.460
- who died last year.
- Amy.

913
00:44:32.461 --> 00:44:33.963
Santos tell you?

914
00:44:34.755 --> 00:44:37.882
- I understand you're helping her out.
- Yeah. on the farm.

915
00:44:37.883 --> 00:44:41.052
I grew up on one. and Amy's...

916
00:44:41.053 --> 00:44:44.974
Mrs. Miller is getting pressure to sell.
so I'm just helping out.

917
00:44:45.891 --> 00:44:48.978
- What about her friends and family?
- Yeah. they're around.

918
00:44:49.770 --> 00:44:52.522
- Supporting her?
- Yeah. I think they try to.

919
00:44:52.523 --> 00:44:54.984
But. mostly. she's just leaning on...

920
00:44:56.277 --> 00:44:57.444
me.

921
00:45:00.781 --> 00:45:03.992
I'm sure she's really grateful
for everything that you do.

922
00:45:03.993 --> 00:45:05.995
but it's important to have boundaries.

923
00:45:06.912 --> 00:45:07.997
Yeah.

924
00:45:11.542 --> 00:45:13.210
Hey. you want to do me a favor?

925
00:45:15.004 --> 00:45:16.004
Yeah?

926
00:45:16.005 --> 00:45:17.506
You want to house-sit for me
while I'm gone?

927
00:45:19.008 --> 00:45:22.845
You'd actually be helping me out.
and you could save some money on rent.

928
00:45:24.138 --> 00:45:25.638
Are you being serious?

929
00:45:25.639 --> 00:45:28.641
No smoking. no parties.
no pets. no babies.

930
00:45:28.642 --> 00:45:30.268
yours or anybody else's.

931
00:45:30.269 --> 00:45:32.438
- I don't have a baby.
- No. but she does.

932
00:45:33.480 --> 00:45:36.357
I was going to ask Abbot.
but he does nude yoga at sunrise.

933
00:45:36.358 --> 00:45:38.151
and I don't think some
of my elderly neighbors

934
00:45:38.152 --> 00:45:39.903
would survive seeing that.

935
00:45:40.779 --> 00:45:43.948
Yeah. Yeah. that would be amazing...

936
00:45:43.949 --> 00:45:47.285
the house-sitting.
not seeing Abbot's naked yoga.

937
00:45:47.286 --> 00:45:49.954
If I don't come back.
you got a swinging bachelor pad.

938
00:45:49.955 --> 00:45:51.165
Okay.

939
00:45:52.791 --> 00:45:54.167
Come find me before you leave.

940
00:45:54.168 --> 00:45:56.670
I'll give you my keys
and the security code.

941
00:45:57.838 --> 00:45:59.590
Who's the joker that did this?

942
00:46:03.427 --> 00:46:04.510
We need some help out there.

943
00:46:04.511 --> 00:46:06.971
You two. make sure
to double-check your work.

944
00:46:06.972 --> 00:46:08.765
Triage could use an extra hand.

945
00:46:08.766 --> 00:46:10.975
Princess. finish up here.
then head that way.

946
00:46:10.976 --> 00:46:14.896
- Three for CT now. Should I run it over?
- No. Keep taking off orders.

947
00:46:14.897 --> 00:46:17.023
CT's gonna get backed up
if we wait on these.

948
00:46:17.024 --> 00:46:19.192
I know. but I can't waste
a runner on that right now.

949
00:46:19.193 --> 00:46:20.610
Where'd you find a carrier sheet?

950
00:46:20.611 --> 00:46:23.946
Exactly where I filed it away
ten years ago.

951
00:46:23.947 --> 00:46:27.701
- I thought that thing didn't work.
- Can't receive. but it can send.

952
00:46:35.709 --> 00:46:38.419
Stay hydrated.
preferably with electrolyte-rich drinks

953
00:46:38.420 --> 00:46:40.546
- like coconut water.
- I'm not a fan of coconuts.

954
00:46:40.547 --> 00:46:42.131
Okay. Gatorade's also an option.

955
00:46:42.132 --> 00:46:44.467
Just avoid alcohol and caffeine.
and I suggest wearing

956
00:46:44.468 --> 00:46:46.219
- light. breathable clothing.
- Boring.

957
00:46:46.220 --> 00:46:49.764
Come back if your symptoms worsen.
if you develop a headache or confusion.

958
00:46:49.765 --> 00:46:50.891
Okay.

959
00:46:52.309 --> 00:46:54.103
You sure about that?

960
00:46:56.230 --> 00:46:57.898
Hey. could you turn that up?

961
00:46:59.733 --> 00:47:02.568
<i>Have responded
to a deadly waterslide collapse</i>

962
00:47:02.569 --> 00:47:03.820
<i>at a local water park.</i>

963
00:47:03.821 --> 00:47:06.155
<i>Now. we're told there's
at least one fatality.</i>

964
00:47:06.156 --> 00:47:07.365
<i>with multiple injuries.</i>

965
00:47:07.366 --> 00:47:10.827
Oh. shit. And they're all coming to us.

966
00:47:10.828 --> 00:47:13.330
<i>Currently being airlifted
to the hospital by heli...</i>

966
00:47:14.305 --> 00:48:14.828
